# FleetPulse layout, scroll, and error guardrails

When editing **root layout** or components that affect **scroll**, **first-load**, or **global error handling**, follow these rules so we don’t repeat the March 2025 breakage.

## Must preserve

1. **Scroll container** — ScrollBlur, FloatingLoginCard, and ScrollToTop use `window.scrollY`. Do **not** add a wrapper around main content that has its own scroll (e.g. `overflow-y: auto` + fixed height). The **document/body** must stay the primary vertical scroll container.

2. **Error scope** — Use **local** error boundaries (e.g. DashboardErrorBoundary) for section failures. Avoid a global ErrorBoundary that catches every error and triggers a full-app reload; if you keep one, reserve it for true top-level failures only.

3. **Intro / first-load** — Any first-load overlay that uses a video or heavy asset must have a **failsafe timeout** and a **fallback or skip** so users never see a blank/purple screen for more than a few seconds.

4. **Asset paths** — After moving or renaming files under `public/` or `components/`, update all references and verify path/casing (e.g. `animations` vs `Animations`).

## Before merging

Run the checklist in **docs/SAFE_CHANGES_GUARDRAILS.md** (landing loads, scroll unblurs, login card collapses, back-to-top, login → dashboard, dashboard loads, asset paths). When changing root layout or global wrappers, compare against **Restore Points/FleetPulseRestoreReference** for scroll and error behavior.

